Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

To make your stock, add the @boiled water{750%ml} for the risotto (see pantry for amount) to a #medium saucepan{} on high heat.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{15%g}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to the lowest setting.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Trim the bottom 2cm from the @asparagus{150%g} and discard. Halve the asparagus widthways.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, garlic and @sun-dried tomato paste{50%g}, then cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

To make your risotto, stir a ladle of stock into the rice. When the stock has been absorbed by the rice, stir in another ladle of stock.

Keep the pan on medium heat and continue stirring in stock, letting it absorb each time.

The cooking time should take ~{20-25%minutes} and your risotto is done when your rice is 'al dente' - cooked through but with a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the risotto has about ~{10%minutes} cooking time left, pop the asparagus and @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

When the risotto is cooked, remove from the heat and mix in the @butter{20%g} and two thirds of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When the veg is roasted, serve the chicken risotto in bowls with the asparagus and tomatoes on top.

Finish with a drizzle of the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} and a sprinkle of the remaining cheese over the top.

Enjoy!